18#include "QRDataMask.h"
19#include "BitMatrix.h"
20#include "ZXContainerAlgorithms.h"
21
22#include <stdexcept>
23
24namespace ZXing {
25namespace QRCode {
26
27namespace {
28
29/**
30* 000: mask bits for which (x + y) mod 2 == 0
31*/
32bool DataMask000(int i, int j)
33{
34 return ((i + j) & 0x01) == 0;
35}
36
37/**
38* 001: mask bits for which x mod 2 == 0
39*/
40bool DataMask001(int i, int)
41{
42 return (i & 0x01) == 0;
43}
44
45/**
46* 010: mask bits for which y mod 3 == 0
47*/
48bool DataMask010(int, int j)
49{
50 return j % 3 == 0;
51}
52
53/**
54* 011: mask bits for which (x + y) mod 3 == 0
55*/
56bool DataMask011(int i, int j)
57{
58 return (i + j) % 3 == 0;
59}
60
61/**
62* 100: mask bits for which (x/2 + y/3) mod 2 == 0
63*/
64bool DataMask100(int i, int j)
65{
66 return (((i / 2) + (j / 3)) & 0x01) == 0;
67}
68
69/**
70* 101: mask bits for which xy mod 2 + xy mod 3 == 0
71* equivalently, such that xy mod 6 == 0
72*/
73bool DataMask101(int i, int j)
74{
75 return (i * j) % 6 == 0;
76}
77
78/**
79* 110: mask bits for which (xy mod 2 + xy mod 3) mod 2 == 0
80* equivalently, such that xy mod 6 < 3
81*/
82bool DataMask110(int i, int j)
83{
84 return ((i * j) % 6) < 3;
85}
86
87/**
88* 111: mask bits for which ((x+y)mod 2 + xy mod 3) mod 2 == 0
89* equivalently, such that (x + y + xy mod 3) mod 2 == 0
90*/
91bool DataMask111(int i, int j)
92{
93 return ((i + j + ((i * j) % 3)) & 0x01) == 0;
94}
95
96using IsMaskedFunc = bool (*)(int, int);
97
98/**
99* See ISO 18004:2006 6.8.1
100*/
101static const IsMaskedFunc DATA_MASKS[] = {
102 DataMask000,
103 DataMask001,
104 DataMask010,
105 DataMask011,
106 DataMask100,
107 DataMask101,
108 DataMask110,
109 DataMask111,
110};
111
112} // anonymous
113
114DataMask::DataMask(int reference)
115{
116 if (reference < 0 || reference >= Size(DATA_MASKS)) {
117 throw std::invalid_argument("Invalid data mask");
118 }
119 _isMasked = DATA_MASKS[reference];
120}
121
122void
123DataMask::unmaskBitMatrix(BitMatrix& bits, int dimension) const
124{
125 for (int i = 0; i < dimension; i++) {
126 for (int j = 0; j < dimension; j++) {
127 if (_isMasked(i, j)) {
128 bits.flip(j, i);
129 }
130 }
131 }
132}
